-- 336_security_function_search_path.sql
-- Pins search_path on every public.* function flagged by Supabase advisor
-- `function_search_path_mutable`. With a mutable search_path, a SECURITY DEFINER
-- function is vulnerable to a malicious caller hijacking unqualified relation
-- names; a fixed search_path eliminates that vector.
--
-- Pure config refactor: function bodies and signatures are unchanged.
-- Idempotent: ALTER FUNCTION ... SET search_path = ... is safe to re-run.
-- Rollback: ALTER FUNCTION ... RESET search_path; per function.

